                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 600.119/545a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Representatives in All Countries</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Circular telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 15, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Two proclamations have been issued today, effective February 16, under which
                    licenses are required for all exports from and all imports into the United
                    States. Copies follow by pouch. Repeat to all consular officers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
